<title>HUNGARY: HUNGARY JAN-MARCH NET WAGES UP 25.7 PCT-STAT.</title>
<headline>HUNGARY JAN-MARCH NET WAGES UP 25.7 PCT-STAT.</headline>
<dateline>BUDAPEST 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Average net monthly wage in the January-March period in Hungary's business sphere rose to 35,820 forints, up 25.7 percent on the similar period of 1996, the Central Statistical Office (KSH) said on Thursday.</p>
<p>This compares to a CPI increase of 18.8 percent over the same period.</p>
<p>KSH added that while-collar workers' wages rose 11.6 percent, while blue collar workers' wages rose 1.6 percent in real terms.</p>
